<section class="faq">
  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  
  <div class="faq-grid">

    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">Do you work with teams in-house or remotely?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">Both. I'm based in Montpellier, France but work with teams globally, and I travel to New York regularly so I can easily work on-site with teams there as well. I've successfully embedded with remote teams and traveled for in-person collaboration when it makes sense.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">Do you take on small projects?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">Yes, audits and research sprints are designed for exactly that. If you just need a second pair of eyes or a quick validation, let's talk.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">What industries do you work with?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">I've worked with e-commerce, travel, telecom, online education and nonprofits. The industry matters less than the problem. I'm most interested in complex UX challenges that require research and strategic thinking.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">How do you charge for your work?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">It depends on the engagement, but I typically work in one of two ways: a retainer with a discounted hourly rate for ongoing work, or a fixed fee with an agreed hour cap for defined projects. I'm happy to talk through which structure makes the most sense for what you need.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">What if I need ongoing support?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">I offer retainer arrangements for teams who want monthly strategy calls, quarterly audits, or ongoing design reviews. This works well for companies who need consistent UX input without a full-time hire.</p>
    </div>

  </div>
